<font color="#FF0000">TAKING CARE OF BUSINESS</font><br>
<tt>Sun Aug 24 22:37:58 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
P-38 that's Sissy-stuff, we used the links off the 7.62 belts, used tracers to light our cigarettes, chewed C-4 like gum, mixed agent orange with our Kool-Aid, ate brown husk rice and added nuoc nam fish sauce to our ham and lima beans. <br><br>
You're still upset on account we found your down chopper, hauled the remains of it to hill 65 and turned the part that had your Special Forces Decal into piss tunes and the remainder into one of those 25 Cents kiddy-Rides. <br>
Charlie still uses it today. Some Marine visited the site a week ago and brought back pictures, of the piss tubes not the kiddy-ride.<br><br>
Then, you guys really got upset when during the Monsoon that Jarhead from California turned the choppers tail-end into surf boards and we came out on them to save the special forces camp at Thung Duc again. <br><br>
Oh! Oh! And remember the time that Marine from Texas ripped off six of your 2.75in rockets from the choppers rocket pod, cause he figured he could fire them from the shoulder position using our bazooka tube. That really upset your CO. <br><br>
And that time a bunch of us got medivacked into Chu Lai and we took three of your brand new Cobra choppers and painted them PINK? <br>
Your CO though that was the color they came in and formed what later became known as &quot;The Special Forces  Pink Team.&quot; <br><br>
Then, then &quot;REAL STORY,&quot; one of your Army 2nd lieutenant advisors was assigned to 3/7 battalion headquarters but no one liked him, not your people not our people, then one night when the hill was getting overrun the Gunny accidentally shot him in the shoulder. The generals debated over that one for the longest time and finally they all settled on giving your guy a Purple Heart and the Gunny a Bronze Star and everybody was happy. True story, it's in the book, only just a little bit different.  Oh! And that Army Catholic Chaplain that was taking a shower when we were mortared during a USO show and one of those go go girls jumped into the same hole the naked chaplain was in. He was the only Chaplain we knew of that got both a Purple Heart and the clap during his tour.<br><br>
And remember that time we left a snake on the chopper for you guys. We sat there in the paddies laughing and laughing with tears coming down our eyes as the special forces chopper did flip flops in the air, trying to get the snake out.<br>

<p><code>-- Special Forces Base Camp 1,2, A-1, a-2, a3   (Sparrowhawk) </code><p>


